writings-hitlers-rise-could-all-happen-again/ |publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |accessdate=June 11, 2014}}</ref>\n* {{cite journal |last=Brat |first=David A. |author2=Kenneth Sands |author3=Evan Dungan |title=NAEP Scores, Human Capital, and State Growth |journal=Virginia Economic Journal |volume=14 |year=2009 |pages=21\u201343}}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Park |first1=Walter G. |author2=David A. Brat |title=A Global Kuznets Curve? |journal=Kyklos |volume=48 |issue=1 |year=1995 |page=105 |doi=10.1111/j.1467-6435.1995.tb02317.x}}\n* {{cite web |title=All Democracies Created Equal? 195 Years Might Matter |url=http://faculty.rmc.edu/dbrat/researchpapers/2004SEinformsDEMOCRACY.pdf |publisher=Randolf-Macon College |accessdate=June 11, 2014}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Brat |first=David |title=Economic Growth and Institutions: The Rise and Fall of the Protestant Ethic? |journal=Virginia Economic Journal |volume=9 |year=2004 |pages=33\u201340}}\n* An Analysis of the Moral Foundations in Ayn Rand <ref>{{cite news |title=So Who's The Guy Who Just Beat Eric Cantor? Meet Dave Brat|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/06/10/dave-brat-eric-cantor_n_5482610.html|publisher=[[The Huffington Post]] |accessdate=June 11, 2014}}</ref>\n* {{cite journal |last=Park |first=Walter G |last2=Brat |first2= David A |title=Cross-Country R&D and Growth: Variations on a Theme of Mankiw-Romer-Weil |journal=Eastern Economic Journal |date=Summer 1996 |volume=22 |issue=3 |pages=345\u201354 |url=http://nw08.american.edu/~wgp/park_eej.pdf |accessdate=June 13, 2014}}\n* {{cite web |title=American Underdog: Proof That Principles Matter |url=https://www.amazon.com/American-Underdog-Proof-Principles-Matter/dp/1455539910 |publisher=Center Street |accessdate=June 27, 2016}} (2016)<ref name=\"Takala Examiner Story\">{{cite news|first=Rudy|last=Takala|authorlink=Rudy Takala|title=Dave Brat to release his first book this week|url=http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/dave-brat-to-release-his-first-book-this-week/article/2594977|publisher=[[The Washington Examiner]] |accessdate=June 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBrat was raised in the [[Presbyterian]] faith and his wife is a [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]].<ref name=\"themorningsun1\"/> Splitting their time between two churches,<ref name=\"themorningsun1\"/> they are parishioners of [[St. Mary's Catholic School (Richmond, Virginia)|St. Mary Catholic Church]] in Richmond.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://davebratforcongress.com/about-dave/ |title=David Brat campaign website |publisher=Davebratforcongress.com |date= |accessdate=June 11, 2014}}</ref> Brat also identifies as a [[Calvinism|Calvinist]] and lists affiliations with Christ Episcopal Church, Third Presbyterian, and Shady Grove Methodist.<ref name=TimesBiblicalViews>{{cite news |last=Dias |first=Elizabeth |date=June 11, 2014 |title=David Brat's Biblical Views Shape His Tea Party Politics |url=http://time.com/2860967/david-brats-biblical-views-shape-his-tea-party-politics/ |work=Time |accessdate=June 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\nBrat moved to Virginia in 1996 with his wife, Laura.<ref>{{cite news |author=June 10, 2014 |url=http://dailyentertainmentnews.com/breaking-news/laura-brat-virginias-7th-congressional-district-politician-dave-brats-wife/ |title=Laura Brat- Virginia Politician Dave Brat's Wife (Bio, Wiki) |publisher=Dailyentertainmentnews.com |date=1962-01-15 |accessdate=2014-06-12}}</ref> They live in [[Glen Allen, Virginia|Glen Allen]], a suburb of Richmond.<ref>{{cite news |title=A look at Eric Cantor, tea party challenger|url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2014/jun/06/a-look-at-eric-cantor-tea-party-challenger/|publisher=Las Vegas Sun|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref> They have two children, Jonathan and Sophia.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Dave Brat|url=http://davebrat.com/about-dave/|website=davebrat.com|publisher=Friends for Dave Bray|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nBrat's brother, Dan, is a [[medical doctor]] specializing in neuropathology.  He also serves as vice-chairman of the Department of [[Pathology]] and Laboratory Medicine at [[Emory University]]. His youngest brother, Jim, is a [[Los Angeles]]-based real estate attorney.<ref name=\"themorningsun1\"/><ref>{{cite news |author=Mark Holmberg |date=June 11, 2014 |url=http://wtvr.com/2014/06/11/holmberg-where-does-the-dave-brat-toppling-of-eric-cantor-rank/ |title=Where does the Dave Brat toppling of Eric Cantor rank? |publisher=[[WTVR-TV]] |accessdate=June 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://brat.house.gov/ Congressman Dave Brat] official U.S. House site\n* [http://davebrat.com/ Dave Brat for Congress]\n* [http://faculty.rmc.edu/dbrat/ Professor David Brat at Randolph-Macon College]\n* {{DMOZ|Regional/North_America/United_States/Virginia/Society_and_Culture/Politics/Candidates_and_Campaigns/US_House/Congressional_District_07/Dave_Brat}}\n* {{C-SPAN|David Brat}}\n{{CongLinks | congbio = B001290| ballot = Dave Brat | nndb = | votesmart = 152270 | govtrack = | opencong = | rollcall = | politifact = | fec = H4VA07143 | opensecrets = | assets = | legistorm = | followthemoney =  | ontheissues =  | congress = dave-brat/2203 | worldcat = | cspan = | imdb = | bloomberg = | nyt = | washpo = }}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{USRepSuccessionBox\n| state=Virginia\n| district=7\n| start=November 4, 2014<!--Term for special elections begin on election day-->\n| before=[[Eric Cantor]]}}\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Alma Adams]]<br><small>D-[[North Carolina]]</small>}}\n{{s-ttl|title=''[[List of current members of the United States House of Representatives by seniority|United States Representatives by seniority]]''|years=370th}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Donald Norcross]]<br><small>D-[[New Jersey]]</small>}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{VA-FedRep}}\n{{USHouseCurrent}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brat, David}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:American Calvinist and Reformed Christians]]\n[[Category:American economists]]\n[[Categor